{
  "text": "Coordinated control of mRNA translation and processing of nascent polypeptides is critical for normal cell function, but the mechanisms that couple these events remain unclear. Deregulated protein synthesis and processing underlie a number of pathological conditions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Insights on how translation and protein processing are connected have been gained on studies of the unfolded protein response, involving secretory and transmembrane proteins, but little is known on cytosolic proteins such as protein kinases [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
